# Tell, Don't Ask

**Tell:** call an intent method (`connect`, `subscribe`, `processConnect`) that owns the decision and state change.

**Don't ask:** avoid `if (session.getStatus() == X) { session.setStatus(Y); … }` spread across callers.

Naming follows [docs/domain-specification.md](../../docs/domain-specification.md). See [stomp4j-law-of-demeter.mdc](stomp4j-law-of-demeter.mdc).

## Layers

```
StompClient API  →  StompClientImpl  →  Transport / Stomp protocol
StompServer      →  Session          →  MessageHandler / SubscriptionHandler
```

- **Public API:** thin facade; delegate to implementation.
- **Session / StompClientImpl:** own connection state machine and frame handling.
- **Handlers:** callbacks for application logic; server tells `MessageHandler.process`, not raw frame parsing.

## Violations vs fixes

```java
// ❌ Caller owns CONNECT transition
if (status == Status.STARTED) {
    status = Status.CONNECTED;
    channel.write(connectedFrame);
}

// ✅ Session owns the transition
session.processConnect(message);
```

## Pragmatic guidance

- Apply on **new or touched** behaviour; do not mandate big-bang refactors.
- When touching legacy ask-then-set code, consolidate into `Session` or `StompClientImpl` in the same change.

## Never

- Duplicate the same state-check + mutation in multiple callers.
- Parse STOMP frames in handler callbacks when `Session` should own protocol logic.
